This fixes **setup.py** and **tox.ini** according to Issue #10

Prevents PIP from complaining about upgrading requests module every time we want to update both **webpreview** and **requests** modules.

@ludbek in order for this to work, the package must be updated on PyPI.

There are some issues with float32. I'd like to see what the test suite is doing.
If problems persist, I will deactivate the new operator for float32.

@asmushetzel

@micheles please have a look too.

See also https://github.com/gem/oq-engine/issues/2023

Full tests (ongoing): https://ci.openquake.org/job/zdevel_oq-engine/1799/

Adding option to include `FILES` variable in model to explicitly specify submodules.

For example:


```
class MyCoolModel(YhatModel):
    FILES = [
        "theoretical/submodule/run.py"
    ]
    def execute(self, data):
        return data
```

### Summary

@mrpau-richard Please review & merge so Julius can pull and continue working off these latest edits.

@mrpau-julius I hope reviewing the changes in this PR can help you continue in the same style. 
**Please remember the correct indentation for Gherkin keywords!**

@Carreau @minrk would you be ok with me adding an intermediate base class called JupyterServerApp between NotebookApp and JupyterApp.

NotebookApp would only have what is specific to the current notebook, and all the rest would be moved up.

The goal is to be able to inherit from this JupyterServerApp in JupyterLabApp eventually.

The h5py dependency was pinned to a fixed version. Thus numpy won't update as it depends on it.

found by
@jenshnielsen

## What do these changes do?

A worker that is assigned a task and blocked in a `ray.get` should release its resources to allow another task to run. Without this, with the following task, you cannot have a recursion deeper than the number of cores available:

```
def recurse(i):
  if i == 0:
    return i
  return ray.get(recurse.remote(i - 1))
```

## Related issue number

This is similar to #286, but for the Raylet.
